<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Tamil Places — Landing Layout</title>
  <style>
    :root{
      --accent:#d4af37;
      --muted:#555;
      --bg:#fafafa;
      --card:#ffffff;
    }
    *{box-sizing:border-box}
    body{
      margin:0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Noto Sans Tamil", sans-serif;
      background:var(--bg);
      color:#222;
    }

    /* Header with 5 place boxes */
    header{
      background:#111;
      color:#fff;
      padding:10px 16px;
    }
    .top-nav{
      display:flex;
      gap:10px;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
    }
    .top-nav .place{
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      padding:8px 14px;
      border-radius:6px;
      font-weight:600;
      min-width:120px;
      text-align:center;
    }
    /* Layout: sidebar + main */
    .container{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:220px 1fr;
      gap:16px;
      padding:16px;
    }

    aside{
      background:var(--card);
      border-radius:8px;
      padding:12px;
      box-shadow:0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.06);
      height:calc(100vh - 96px);
    }
    nav ul{ list-style:none; padding:0; margin:0; }
    nav li{
      padding:10px 8px;
      border-radius:6px;
      margin-bottom:8px;
      cursor:pointer;
    }
    nav li:hover{ background:#f0f0f0; }
    nav li strong{ color:var(--accent); }

    main{
      min-height:80vh;
    }

    .hero{
      background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(212,175,55,0.08), rgba(255,255,255,0));
      padding:18px;
      border-radius:8px;
      margin-bottom:12px;
      box-shadow:0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
    }
    article.card{
      background:var(--card);
      padding:14px;
      margin-bottom:14px;
      border-radius:8px;
      box-shadow:0 1px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
    }
    article.card h2{ margin:0 0 8px; color:#111; }
    article.card h3{ margin:10px 0 6px; font-size:1rem; color:var(--muted); }
    article.card p{ margin:6px 0; line-height:1.5; color:#333; }

    .meta{ font-size:.9rem; color:#666; }

    /* Responsive */
    @media (max-width:800px){
      .container{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
      aside{ height:auto; order:2; }
      main{ order:1; }
      .top-nav .place{ min-width:100px; padding:6px 10px;}
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <div class="top-nav" role="navigation" aria-label="Top places in Tamil">
      <!-- Five Tamil place names -->
      <div class="place">சென்னை</div>
      <div class="place">கோயம்புத்தூர்</div>
      <div class="place">மதுரை</div>
      <div class="place">திருச்சி</div>
      <div class="place">நாகப்பட்டினம்</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- Left sidebar -->
    <aside aria-label="Sidebar menu">
      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>வாருங்கள்</strong> — Explore</li>
          <li>புகைப்படங்கள் — Gallery</li>
          <li>வரலாறு — History</li>
          <li>உறுப்பினர் — Members</li>
          <li>தொடரை — Contact</li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <main>
      <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
        <h1 id="hero-title">தமிழ் இடங்கள் — Discover Tamil Places</h1>
        <p class="meta">A short landing overview. Below are two featured articles that describe three places each.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Article 1: talks about three places -->
      <article class="card" aria-labelledby="a1-title">
        <h2 id="a1-title">Article 1 — Coastal & Heritage Highlights</h2>

        <h3>சென்னை (Chennai)</h3>
        <p>Chennai is the capital city on the east coast. It is known for its long Marina Beach, temples, and rich cultural life.</p>

        <h3>நாகப்பட்டினம் (Nagapattinam)</h3>
        <p>Nagapattinam is a coastal town with historic temples and traditional fishing communities. Its shoreline carries stories of trade and sea routes.</p>

        <h3>மதுரை (Madurai)</h3>
        <p>Madurai is famous for the Meenakshi Amman Temple and a long cultural history, with festivals and classical arts practiced across generations.</p>
      </article>

      <!-- Article 2: talks about three places -->
      <article class="card" aria-labelledby="a2-title">
        <h2 id="a2-title">Article 2 — Rivers, Temples & Crafts</h2>

        <h3>திருச்சி (Tiruchirappalli)</h3>
        <p>Tiruchirappalli sits on the banks of the Kaveri River and hosts many ancient temples and rock-cut monuments.</p>

        <h3>கோயம்புத்தூர் (Coimbatore)</h3>
        <p>Coimbatore is an industrial and textile hub also close to scenic hill stations; it blends modern growth with local craftsmanship.</p>

        <h3>சென்னை (Chennai) — revisit</h3>
        <p>Chennai's cultural scene supports music, Bharatanatyam, and theatre that influence the surrounding towns and educational centers.</p>
      </article>

      <!-- Main three paragraphs that talk about another article (reference) -->
      <section class="card" aria-labelledby="ref-title">
        <h2 id="ref-title">More on Article 2 — A Closer Look</h2>
        <p>Article 2 highlights how rivers and trade shaped the local crafts and temple architectures. These features are strongly visible in Tiruchirappalli and Madurai, where river life connects villages and markets.</p>
        <p>The textile legacy in Coimbatore (mentioned in Article 2) supports cottage industries in nearby towns. Many families rely on these skills passed down through generations.</p>
        <p>By studying Article 2 and visiting the listed places, you get a layered view — history, religion, and modern livelihoods — all tied to Tamil culture and goldsmithing traditions that still thrive today.</p>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
